The Programs will be submitted as a single directory containing   install_dependencies.sh
compile.sh
run.sh
...  Your program needs to set itself up on a fresh install of Ubuntu 14.04.  install_dependencies.sh  should downloadany libraries and supporting files your program needs, and  compile.sh  will compile your program, if that's necessary. These will not be timed. The third must be set up so that it accepts a directory of png images.  run.sh path/to/directory/containing/images  This is the portion of your project that will be timed.  The program must output JSON Array that pairs the filenames in the directory with a "1" (yes) /"0" (no) for whether a stop-sign is present or not present in the image respectively. A sample output  is shown below:  run.sh path/to/directory/containing/images 
[
    {   
     filename :  college_ave_stopsighn.png ,
         stop_sign :  1 
    }, 
    {
     filename :  hippopotamus.png ,
     stop_sign :  no 
    }
]
